# 4. がんばればきっと

Airi: You want to be an idol? Are you serious?
Minori: Y-Yes! I'm practicing for an audition right now!
Airi: And where is your audition at?
Minori: Oh, I was planning on auditioning for MoriPro next!
Airi: MoriPro?! That's a major talent agency!
Airi: Do you have any idea how low their acceptance rate is?! An amateur like you would be lucky to even pass their initial screening!
Minori: I, uh...
Airi: What's your name?
Minori: M-Minori Hanasato.
Airi: How many auditions have you had before? How'd you do?
Minori: I've applied about fifty times so far and passed the initial application screening about three times...
Minori: But...I haven't managed to get further than that, yet...
Airi: Sigh...
Airi: And you honestly think you have a chance at MoriPro?! I doubt you even have a shot with the smaller agencies.
Minori: S-Still! I want to try harder!
Minori: If I dedicate myself, I'm sure I can do it! More, more, more!
Haruka: .....
Airi: That's it?
Airi: Things don't just happen because you really want them to!
Minori: Huh?
Airi: You'd be better off giving up now. You don't seem like the idol type.
Minori: How can you say that...
Shizuku: Airi, stop...
Airi: What?
Shizuku: You shouldn't just deny someone's dreams like that.
Shizuku: You may no longer be actively working, but you're still an idol who's meant to give everyone hope.
Airi: !!
Shizuku: I don't like it when you say things like that, Airi.
Airi: I know that! Really, I do...
Haruka: .....
Minori: Even so, I'm still going to give it my best!
Airi: And I'm saying that won't matter!
Minori: Well, I have faith!
Airi: Faith?
Minori: Tomorrow will always be a better day!
Minori: So in order to help everyone believe things can always get better...
Minori: I'm here to give everyone hope for a better tomorrow! Those are the words that guide me!
Haruka: That's...
Minori: And that's why I'm not ever giving up, no matter the odds! I will keep giving more until I pass! More, more!
???: <Hehe♪>
Minori: Huh?
???: <Such a lovely, heartfelt speech!>
Airi: Wh-Who was that?! Is somebody else up here?
Minori: Huh? My phone lit up?
Miku: <It's nice to meet you, Minori!>
Minori: Huh?! A hologram of... Miku?!
Miku: <It looks like Haruka, Airi, and Shizuku are with you. I'm glad to see you're all here♪>
Haruka: What's going on? Is Miku talking to us right now? And how does she know our names?
Miku: <Hehe! That's because I've come from a world born from all of your feelings, SEKAI!>
Shizuku: A world born from our feelings?
Miku: <That's right! Rin and I are actually getting ready to start a show at this very moment!>
Miku: <Rin is a great dancer, you know. I even ask her for help with my moves from time to time.>
Minori: With your moves? Oh!
Miku: <Oops! The show's about to start! Gotta go!>
Miku: <Anyway, we'll be waiting here for you! I hope you can all join us soon!>
Airi: Wh-What was that? Some new kind of ad?
Shizuku: It feels a little strange actually speaking with Miku like that.
Minori: U-Um, excuse me!
Airi: What now?
Minori: O-Oh, um... I just... That Miku advertisement... Or was it an advertisement? Anyway, what Miku said made me think, um...
Shizuku: Are you all right? Try not to be so nervous.
Minori: Oh, right! Breathe in... Breathe out... Sorry about that. It's just... I have a favor to ask.
Minori: If it's not too much trouble, could you help me practice?!
Airi: What?!
